    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-02T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-02T12:00:00-05:00" n="538"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/1–252: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the United States Delegation to the
                        General Assembly</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-02T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 2, 1952—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 814. Position paper <gloss
                        target="#t_SD1">SD</gloss>/A/C.3/147,<note n="1" xml:id="d538fn1">See
                        footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_822">p. 822</ref>.</note> para 3, recommends
                        <gloss target="#t_USGADel1">USGADel</gloss> oppose authorization for High
                    Commissioner for Refugees appeal to govts or make general appeal for funds.
                    Staff recommends that, if proposed, <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> authorize
                    HC appeal only to individuals and <gloss target="#t_NGO1">NGO</gloss>’s would
                    help counteract effect of <gloss target="#t_USGADel1">USGADel</gloss> negative
                    position on (1) appeal to govts and on (2) sizeable increase in HC’s budget.</p>
                <p>Advise soonest. Vote may be taken January 4 or 5.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
